# Public HTTPS Caddy example for NRD
# ----------------------------------
# Purpose:
#   - Expose NRD publicly with automatic HTTPS.
#   - Use only if you intentionally want internet access to the dashboard.
#
# Replace these before use:
#   - nrd.example.com -> your real public domain
#   - your@email.com  -> your real email for ACME notices
#
# Requirements:
#   - DNS A/AAAA record for nrd.example.com must point to your droplet.
#   - Ports 80 and 443 must be open to the internet.
#   - Strongly consider setting NRD_ADMIN_TOKEN before using a public endpoint.
#
# Browser URL:
#   https://nrd.example.com
#
# Typical NRD runtime for this mode:
#   HOST=127.0.0.1 PORT=8080 cargo run
{
    email your@email.com
}

nrd.example.com {
    encode gzip zstd
    reverse_proxy 127.0.0.1:8080

    header {
        Strict-Transport-Security "max-age=31536000; includeSubDomains; preload"
        X-Content-Type-Options nosniff
        Referrer-Policy same-origin
        X-Frame-Options SAMEORIGIN
    }
}
